---
import Mascot from './Mascot.astro';
---

<section class="lead-magnet-section" aria-labelledby="site-next-step-title">
  <div class="shell lead-magnet-shell" data-reveal>
    <div class="lead-magnet-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Start with your current process</p>
      <h2 id="site-next-step-title">See what Quid could handle behind the scenes.</h2>
      <p class="lead-magnet-lede">Quid works around your existing inquiry form, inbox, tour calendar, and lead system. Your team sees only what needs attention and keeps the conversations that need a person.</p>
      <div class="lead-magnet-resource">
        <h3>What changes for your team</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span>Fewer missed inquiries</li>
          <li><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span>More booked tours</li>
          <li><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span>Less inbox and calendar chasing</li>
          <li><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span>No CRM migration</li>
          <li><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span>No extra daily tool for frontline staff</li>
          <li><span aria-hidden="true">✓</span>More time for residents and families</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lead-magnet-form-wrap">
      <Mascot pose="summary" class="lead-magnet-mascot" alt="Quid keeping routine admissions work moving behind the scenes" width={190} />
      <div class="lead-magnet-form">
        <div class="lead-magnet-form-heading">
          <span>Choose a useful next step</span>
          <h3>Start with a two-minute check.</h3>
        </div>
        <p>Grade the visible path from website inquiry to booked tour, or show us your current process and we will map where Quid fits.</p>
        <a class="button lead-magnet-submit" href="/senior-living-inquiry-flow-grader/">Grade Your Inquiry Flow</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="/meet-quid/">See How Quid Fits</a>
        <p class="lead-magnet-privacy">No resident information required. The grader runs in your browser and does not store your answers.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
